{"title_page": "Jamia Darul Uloom, Karachi", "text_new": "{{short description|Islamic seminary in Pakistan}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use Pakistani English|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name              = Jamia Darul Uloom Karachi\n| native_name       = {{lang|ur|{{Nastaliq|\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u06c1 \u062f\u0627\u0631\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0648\u0645 \u06a9\u0631\u0627\u0686\u06cc}}}}\n| image_name        = \n| image_size        = 200px\n| established       = 1951 (1370 [[Hijri year|AH]])\n| type              = [[Darul uloom|Islamic university]]\n| affiliation       = [[Wifaq al-Madaris al-`Arabiyah, Pakistan]]\n| president         = [[Muhammad Rafi Usmani]]\n| vice-president    = [[Muhammad Taqi Usmani]]\n| academic_staff    = 210 \n| students          = 10,000\n| city              = [[Korangi]], [[Karachi]]\n| province          = [[Sindh]]\n| country           = [[Pakistan]]\n| coor              = {{coord|24|50|44.74|N|67|9|55.17|E|region:PK_type:edu|display=inline,title}}\n| campus            = [[urban area|Urban]] (56 acres) \n| website           = {{URL|www.darululoomkarachi.edu.pk}}\n}}\n{{Deobandi}}\n\n'''Jamia Darul Uloom Karachi''' ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u06c1 \u062f\u0627\u0631\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0648\u0645 \u06a9\u0631\u0627\u0686\u06cc}}}}, ''J\u0101mi\u2018ah-yi D\u0101ru\u2019l-\u2018Ul\u016bm-i Kar\u0101ch\u012b''; {{lang-ar|\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629 \u062f\u0627\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0648\u0645 \u0643\u0631\u0627\u062a\u0634\u064a}}, ''Jami\u2018ah D\u0101r al-\u2018Ul\u016bm Kar\u0101tsh\u012b'') is an [[Islamic seminary]] in [[Karachi, Pakistan]]. It continues the tradition of the [[Darul uloom]] system initiated by [[Darul Uloom Deoband]] (the largest Sunni Hanafi Deobandi Fiqh following Madarsa).<ref>[https://www.dawn.com/news/1079495 Madressahs and myths] ''Dawn'' (newspaper), Published 10 January 2014, Retrieved 25 February 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.thenews.com.pk/archive/print/519350-religious-leaders-to-politicians-fight-within-legal-limits Religious leaders to politicians: fight within legal limits] The News International (newspaper), Published 13 August 2014, Retrieved 25 February 2020</ref>\n\nThe secondary schools have individual faculties for both boys and girls. The school has the highest standards of Islamic education and offers a combined curriculum covering traditional Islamic studies and contemporary academic subjects.\n\n==History==\nThe seminary was started by the late Mufti Muhammad Shafi and Maulana Noor Ahmad in 1951.<ref>[https://www.deoband.org/2011/12/history/biographies-of-scholars/shaykh-muhammad-shafi\u2018-the-mufti-of-pakistan/ Mufti Muhammad Shafi: The Grand Mufti of Pakistan] Deoband.org website, Published 4 December 2011, Retrieved 25 February 2020</ref> He was previously associated with Darul Uloom Deoband, where he served as the Grand Mufti, but moved to Pakistan following the [[independence of Pakistan]] in 1947. The president of Darul Uloom Karachi is the [[Grand Mufti]] of [[Pakistan]], [[Muhammad Rafi Usmani]]; the [[Vice President]] is [[Muhammad Taqi Usmani]]. Both are the sons of the founder, Mufti [[Muhammad Shafi Deobandi]] (25 January 1897 &ndash; 6 October 1976).<ref>[https://www.themuslim500.com/profiles/muhammad-taqi-usmani/ Muhammad Taqi Usmani &ndash; Leading scholar for the Deobandis and in Islamic finance] The Muslim500 website, Retrieved 25 February 2020</ref>\n\n==Departments==\nThe [[Jamiah]] has the following departments:\n* Nazirah-e- [[Qur'an]] (reading the [[Qur'an]])\n* Tahfeez-ul-[[Qur'an]] (memorizing the Noble [[Qur'an]])\n* [[Tajweed]] (Quranic Phonetics)\n* Department of [[Islamic]] [[Economics]]\n* Department of [[Islamic Law]]\n* Department of [[Islamic Jurisprudence]]\n* Department of [[Hadith]]\n* Department of [[Tafsir]]\n* Department of [[English Language]]\n* Department of [[Politics]]   \n* Department of [[Arabic Language]]\n* Department of [[Information Technology]]\n* Department of [[Business Management]] (in collaboration with Pakistan Institute of Management)<ref name=ArabNews>{{cite news|url=https://www.arabnews.com/node/1471751/pakistan |author=Naimat Khan|date=24 March 2019|title=In a first, Karachi madrassa offers business management course to its students |newspaper=Arab News (newspaper)|accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.darululoomkarachi.edu.pk Official website]\n*[http://www.muftitaqiusmani.edu.pk Mufti Muhammad Taqi Usmani Official website]\n*[http://www.sukkurvi.edu.pk Mufti Abdur Rauf Sukkurvi Official website]\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Islamic universities and colleges in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Karachi]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1951]]\n[[Category:1951 establishments in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Deobandi Islamic universities and colleges]]\n\n\n{{Islam-stub}}\n{{Pakistan-university-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Islamic seminary in Pakistan}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use Pakistani English|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name              = Jamia Darul Uloom Karachi\n| native_name       = {{lang|ur|{{Nastaliq|\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u06c1 \u062f\u0627\u0631\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0648\u0645 \u06a9\u0631\u0627\u0686\u06cc}}}}\n| image_name        = \n| image_size        = 200px\n| established       = 1951 (1370 [[Hijri year|AH]])\n| type              = [[Darul uloom|Islamic university]]\n| affiliation       = [[Wifaq al-Madaris al-`Arabiyah, Pakistan]]\n| president         = [[Muhammad Rafi Usmani]]\n| vice-president    = [[Muhammad Taqi Usmani]]\n| academic_staff    = 210 \n| students          = 10,000\n| city              = [[Korangi]], [[Karachi]]\n| province          = [[Sindh]]\n| country           = [[Pakistan]]\n| coor              = {{coord|24|50|44.74|N|67|9|55.17|E|region:PK_type:edu|display=inline,title}}\n| campus            = [[urban area|Urban]] (56 acres) \n| website           = {{URL|www.darululoomkarachi.edu.pk}}\n}}\n{{Deobandi}}\n\n'''Jamia Darul Uloom Karachi''' ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u06c1 \u062f\u0627\u0631\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0648\u0645 \u06a9\u0631\u0627\u0686\u06cc}}}}, ''J\u0101mi\u2018ah-yi D\u0101ru\u2019l-\u2018Ul\u016bm-i Kar\u0101ch\u012b''; {{lang-ar|\u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629 \u062f\u0627\u0631 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0648\u0645 \u0643\u0631\u0627\u062a\u0634\u064a}}, ''Jami\u2018ah D\u0101r al-\u2018Ul\u016bm Kar\u0101tsh\u012b'') is an [[Islamic seminary]] in [[Karachi, Pakistan]]. It continues the tradition of the [[Darul uloom]] system initiated by [[Darul Uloom Deoband]] (the largest Sunni Hanafi Deobandi Fiqh following Madarsa).<ref>[https://www.dawn.com/news/1079495 Madressahs and myths] ''Dawn'' (newspaper), Published 10 January 2014, Retrieved 25 February 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.thenews.com.pk/archive/print/519350-religious-leaders-to-politicians-fight-within-legal-limits Religious leaders to politicians: fight within legal limits] The News International (newspaper), Published 13 August 2014, Retrieved 25 February 2020</ref>\n\nThe secondary schools have individual faculties for both boys and girls. The school has the highest standards of Islamic education and offers a combined curriculum covering traditional Islamic studies and contemporary academic subjects.\n\n==History==\nThe seminary was started by the late Mufti Muhammad Shafi and Maulana Noor Ahmad in 1951.<ref>[https://www.deoband.org/2011/12/history/biographies-of-scholars/shaykh-muhammad-shafi\u2018-the-mufti-of-pakistan/ Mufti Muhammad Shafi: The Grand Mufti of Pakistan] Deoband.org website, Published 4 December 2011, Retrieved 25 February 2020</ref>He was previously associated with Darul Uloom Deoband, where he served as the Grand Mufti, but moved to Pakistan following the [[independence of Pakistan]] in 1947. The president of Darul Uloom Karachi is the [[Grand Mufti]] of [[Pakistan]], [[Muhammad Rafi Usmani]]; the [[Vice President]] is [[Muhammad Taqi Usmani]]. Both are the sons of the founder, Mufti [[Muhammad Shafi Deobandi]] (25 January 1897 &ndash; 6 October 1976).<ref>[https://www.themuslim500.com/profiles/muhammad-taqi-usmani/ Muhammad Taqi Usmani &ndash; Leading scholar for the Deobandis and in Islamic finance] The Muslim500 website, Retrieved 25 February 2020</ref>\n\n==Departments==\nThe [[Jamiah]] has the following departments:\n* Nazirah-e- [[Qur'an]] (reading the [[Qur'an]])\n* Tahfeez-ul-[[Qur'an]] (memorizing the Noble [[Qur'an]])\n* [[Tajweed]] (Quranic Phonetics)\n* Department of [[Islamic]] [[Economics]]\n* Department of [[Islamic Law]]\n* Department of [[Islamic Jurisprudence]]\n* Department of [[Hadith]]\n* Department of [[Tafsir]]\n* Department of [[English Language]]\n* Department of [[Politics]]   \n* Department of [[Arabic Language]]\n* Department of [[Information Technology]]\n* Department of [[Business Management]] (in collaboration with Pakistan Institute of Management)<ref name=ArabNews>{{cite news|url=https://www.arabnews.com/node/1471751/pakistan |author=Naimat Khan|date=24 March 2019|title=In a first, Karachi madrassa offers business management course to its students |newspaper=Arab News (newspaper)|accessdate=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.darululoomkarachi.edu.pk Official website]\n*[http://www.muftitaqiusmani.edu.pk Mufti Muhammad Taqi Usmani Official website]\n*[http://www.sukkurvi.edu.pk Mufti Abdur Rauf Sukkurvi Official website]\n\n[[Category:Islamic universities and colleges in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Karachi]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1951]]\n[[Category:1951 establishments in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Deobandi Islamic universities and colleges]]\n\n\n{{Islam-stub}}\n{{Pakistan-university-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe